(a)     “Academic Council” means the Academic Connell of the University;
(b)     “Authority” means any of the Authorities of the University specified in
section 24;
(c)      “Board” means the Board of Governors of the University;
(d)      “Chancellor” means the Chancellor of the University;
(e)     “Chairperson” means the head of a Teaching department of the University;
(f)     “Commission” means the Higher Education Commission set up under the
Higher Education Commission Ordinance, 2002 (LIII of 2002);
(g)     “Company” means “ABLE LEARNING (PRIVATE) LIMITED”,
registered under the companies Act, 2017 (XIX of 2017);
(h)     “Constituent Unit” means an institute or college, by whatever name
described, maintained, and administered by the University;
(i)     “Dean” means the head of a Faculty of the University;
(j)     “Department” means a teaching department of the University;
(k)    “Director” means the administrative head of a constituent college or
institute or school or campus of the University;
(l)    “Faculty” means the faculty of the University;
(m)    “Government” means the Federal Government;
(n)    “IUHT” means the Islamabad University of Health Sciences and Emerging
Technologies, Islamabad,
(o)    “Patron” means the Patron of the University;
(p)    “Prescribed” means prescribed by Statutes, Regulations or Rules made under
this Act;
(q)    “Principal” means Principal of a Constituent Unit of the University;
(r)    “Pro Vice Chancellor” means Pro-Vice-Chancellor of the University;
(s)   “Search Committee” means the Search Committee set up by the Board of
Governors under this Act;
(t)   “Statues”, “Regulations” and “Rules”              means   prescribed Statutes,
Regulations and Rules made under this Act;
(u)    “Teacher” means Professor, Associate Professor, Assistant Professor,
Lecturer, Demonstrator and Instructor engaged whole-time by the University
or by its constituent Campus, College, Institute and such other persons as may
be declared to be as teacher by Regulations;
(v)    “University” means Islamabad University of Health Sciences and Emerging
Technologies (IUHT); and
(w)    “Vice Chancellor” means the Vice-Chancellor of the University.

powers and functions:―
(a)     to provide for instruction in such branches of learning as it may deem fit and
to make provisions for teaching, research and development of technologies
and for the advancement and dissemination of knowledge in such other fields
or branches of study as the Board of Governors may determine;
(b)     to make provisions for research and other services for the advancement and
dissemination of knowledge in such a manner as it may determine;
(c)     to institute programs for the exchange of students and teachers between the
University and Higher Education Institutes inside as well as outside Pakistan;
(d)      to prescribe courses of studies in health, sciences, emerging technologies and
such other branches of learning as the university may determine;
(e)    to select, admit, teach, and examine students;
(f)   to hold examinations and confer on or award degrees, diplomas, certificates,
and other academic distinctions to and on persons who have passed its
examinations under prescribed conditions;
(g)   to confer honorary degrees and distinctions on approved persons in the manner
prescribed;
(h)   to enter into agreements, contracts and arrangements with universities,
organizations, institutions, bodies, and individuals for the purpose of carrying
out functions and activities in Pakistan or abroad;
(i)   to establish faculties, teaching departments, campuses, colleges, institutes,
museums, and other centers of learning for the development of teaching and
research and to make such arrangements for their maintenance, management
and administration as it may prescribe;
(j)   to institute Professorship, Associate Professorship, Assistant Professorship,
Lectureship, and any other posts and to appoint person thereto;
(k)   to provide and support the academic developments for the faculty of the
University;
(1)   to decide teaching methods and strategies to ensure the most effective
educational and training programs;
(m)   to institute and award fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, bursaries,
medals, and prizes under prescribed conditions;
(n)   to create posts for teaching, research, administration, and other related
functions and to appoint persons thereto;
(o)   to receive and manage property transferred and grants, bequests, trusts, gifts,
donations, endowment, and other contributions made to it, and invest any
funds representing such property, grants, bequests, trusts, gifts, donations,
endowments, or contributions. To convert one kind of property into another,
in such a manner as it may deem tit;
(p)    to develop and implement fund raising plans;
(q)   to demand and receive fees and other charges as it lay determine;
(r)   to appoint members of various bodies and committees, as the Board may
determine, for academic, administrative, and co-curricular activities;
(s)   to appoint such officers and members of the staff as necessary and prescribe
terms and conditions and powers and duties of such officers and staff;
(t)    to establish and support teaching hospitals;
(u)    to supervise and control the discipline of the students of the University and to
promote extra-curricular and recreational activities of students and to make
arrangements for promoting their health;
(v)      to provide career counseling and job search services to its students and
alumni;
(w)     to maintain linkages with alumni; and
(x)     to do all such other acts and things as may be requisite to further the objectives
of the University as a place of promotion of education, learning and research.

