(i)     the University fees and other charges;
(j)     efficiency and discipline of the employees of the University;
(k)     acquisition and administration of properties and investments of the University;
(l)     constitution, functions, and powers of the Authorities of the University; and
(m)     all other matters which under this act are required to be or may be prescribed
or regulated by Statutes.
(2) The draft of the Statutes shall be proposed the Board and sent for approval to the
Chancellor.
(3) The Chancellor shall have the powers to assent to the statutes submitted to him or refer
them back to the Board for review or reconsideration.
(4) No statute shall be valid unless approved by the Chancellor.

Council may make Regulations, for all or any of the following matters, namely:—
(a)     syllabi and courses of study and research programs leading to degrees,
diplomas or certificates;
(b)     schemes of studies and research, including the duration of courses, number of
subjects or papers for examination;
(c)     courses of studies for degrees, diplomas and certificates of the University;
(d)     methodology for selection and admission of students and determination of
fees and other charges for admission to various courses and examinations;
(e)     admission and expulsion of students to and from the University;
(f)     conduct and supervision of examinations;
(g)     conditions under which a person may carry on independent research to entitle
him to a degree;
(h)     the conditions under which students shall be admitted to the courses and the
examinations of the University and shall become eligible for the award of
degrees, diplomas, and certificates;
(i)     institution of fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals, prizes and
financial assistance;
(j)     conduct of convocation and form of costumes;
(k)     maintenance of discipline among students;
(l)     formation of Faculties, Departments and Board of Studies; and
(m)     all other academic matters under this Act or the Statutes, are to be or may be
prescribed by Regulations.
(2) Regulations shall be proposed by the Academic Council and shall be submitted to the
Board, which may approve them or withhold approval or refer them back to the Academic Council
for reconsideration.
(3) Regulation proposed by the Academic Council shall not be effective unless it receives the
approval of the Board of Governors.
